### Step 5: New CLI Command -- `setup-neural-search`

**New file:** `/Users/4thwithme/Documents/repo/recommendations-service/src/modules/cli/commands/setup-neural-search.command.ts`

**Design decision:** Separate command (not a flag on `reindex-products-neural`). Model setup is a one-time/rare operation (register + deploy model, create pipelines). Reindexing is frequent (weekly). Conflating them creates risk of accidentally re-registering the model.

**Command structure:**

```typescript
import { Logger } from '@nestjs/common';
import { Command, CommandRunner, Option } from 'nest-commander';

import { EnvConfigService } from '@modules/env-config/env-config.service';
import { OpensearchService } from '@modules/opensearch/opensearch.service';

import { OPENSEARCH_INDEX_NAME } from '@constants/env-variables.constant';

import { CronJobExecution } from '@decorators/cron-job-execution.decorator';

interface SetupNeuralSearchOptions {
  modelFormat?: 'TORCH_SCRIPT' | 'ONNX';
  skipClusterSettings?: boolean;
  skipModelSetup?: boolean;
  skipPipelines?: boolean;
}

@Command({
  name: 'setup-neural-search',
  description: 'Register and deploy ML model, create ingest and search pipelines for neural search',
})
export class SetupNeuralSearchCommand extends CommandRunner {
  private readonly logger = new Logger(SetupNeuralSearchCommand.name);
  private isShuttingDown = false;

  constructor(
    private readonly opensearchService: OpensearchService,
    private readonly configService: EnvConfigService,
  ) {
    super();
    this.setupGracefulShutdown();
  }

  @CronJobExecution({ jobName: 'setup-neural-search' })
  async run(
    _passedParams: string[],
    options: SetupNeuralSearchOptions,
  ): Promise<void> {
    // Step 1: Configure cluster ML settings (unless --skip-cluster-settings)
    // Step 2: Register model group "neural_search_model_group"
    // Step 3: Register model "huggingface/sentence-transformers/all-distilroberta-v1" v1.0.1
    //         - Poll via waitForTask until COMPLETED
    //         - Extract model_id from task result
    // Step 4: Deploy model
    //         - Poll via waitForTask until COMPLETED
    // Step 5: Create ingest pipeline "products-neural-pipeline"
    //         - source: combined_text_for_embedding -> target: product_embedding
    // Step 6: Create search pipeline "hybrid-search-pipeline"
    //         - normalization: min_max, combination: arithmetic_mean, weights: [0.3, 0.7]
    // Step 7: Log the model_id for the user to set in OPENSEARCH_MODEL_ID
  }
}
```

**Options:**

| Flag | Description | Default |
|---|---|---|
| `-f, --model-format <format>` | Model format: TORCH_SCRIPT or ONNX | TORCH_SCRIPT |
| `--skip-cluster-settings` | Skip cluster ML settings configuration | false |
| `--skip-model-setup` | Skip model registration and deployment | false |
| `--skip-pipelines` | Skip pipeline creation | false |

**Important output:** After model registration+deployment, the command logs the resulting `model_id` to stdout with a clear message like:

```
Neural search setup completed.
Model ID: <model_id>
ACTION REQUIRED: Set OPENSEARCH_MODEL_ID=<model_id> in your .env file.
```

**Usage:**
```bash
npm run cli:dev -- setup-neural-search                     # full setup
npm run cli:dev -- setup-neural-search -f ONNX             # use ONNX format
npm run cli:dev -- setup-neural-search --skip-model-setup  # only create pipelines
```

**Graceful shutdown:** Same pattern as existing commands (SIGTERM/SIGINT/SIGHUP/SIGQUIT handlers, `isShuttingDown` flag).

